Bad weather in Gulf could threaten BP oil spill site The Development Driller II has been drilling one of the two relief wells Experts are considering whether a possible tropical storm could disrupt work at the site of the BP oil spill .

If bad weather over the Caribbean strengthens and then moves to the site in the Gulf of Mexico , ships will have to be withdrawn .
