A final piece of casing needs to be cemented in place at the bottom of the relief well before it can then drill into the damaged well .
Once the casing is in place , engineers could begin the last drilling within <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DURATION" value="P5D">five</TIMEX3> to <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DURATION" value="P7D">seven days</TIMEX3> and then ` ` kill '' the well with mud and cement .
